text: Pucaccocha (possibly from Quechua puka red, qucha lake, "red lake") is a mountain in the Andes of Peru, about high It is located in the Cusco Region, Calca Province, Lares District. It lies in the eastern extensions of the Urubamba mountain range, northeast of Sahuasiray. == References == Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Cusco Region
